      </userestrict>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_3c35e37f04b69547245dfaf65e0e2b80">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>This collection is open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <bioghist id="aspace_811d79372107df6c649c76a003d9c412">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Ronald Roseman was a renowned oboist and faculty member at Yale for years. He also taught at SUNY Stonybrook, Queens, and Juilliard. He was an active chamber musician and performed widely in New York City and elsewhere.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <prefercite id="aspace_66d122950786b21b5886b8c3d6541601">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>MSS 159, Ronald Roseman Collection in the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_3a4e555bd77095de035d2e5ca4706631">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is organized in three series: I. CD copies of digitized reel-to-reels and cassettes. II. Digitized reel-to-reels and cassettes (originals). III. Reel to reels, not digitized.</p>
      </arrangement>
